meanings.definition: To incorrectly enroll or register in a program or course.
meanings.sent1: She kept misenrolling in the wrong classes every semester.
meanings.sent2: Students sometimes misenroll due to confusion about the registration process.
meanings.sent3: After misenrolling in advanced calculus, he realized he was in over his head.
meanings.sent4: Her habit of misenrolling was like constantly getting lost in a maze of course options.
meanings.sent5: The consequences of misenrolling can lead to academic setbacks and delays.

meanings.definition: The act of mistakenly enrolling in a program or course.
meanings.sent1: His repeated misenrolling caused scheduling conflicts.
meanings.sent2: Misenrolling can result in having to drop classes later on.
meanings.sent3: The comedy of errors began with a simple misenrolling in pottery class.
meanings.sent4: Her misenrolling became a cautionary tale among her friends.
meanings.sent5: The school's system prevented misenrolling by requiring advisor approval.
